caption: First time there. Staff were great. Masks and social distancing enforced. Place clean. Bathrooms were clean too. Cleanliness was great.

My daughter placed an order  for pick up today and the food was AWFUL. schedule a pick up time an hour after placing the order and I’m pretty sure they made it right away as it was cold. The Mac and cheese was completely discolored. Like it was from days ago and it tasted awful. It was closer to a brown color than what we’ve always gotten from there. The sandwich was tough and the turkey dry. Cheese was solidified. Definitely won’t come back to this location. Simple order too.

I would think for a relatively new location the service would be on point. However, the service at this location (unlike other locations in the area) was not good. When we ordered a basic sandwhich with double meat, they got the meat wrong. Then when they remade the sandwhich and we reiterated that we wanted double meat and they gave us a sandwhich with even less than regular portion. When we asked for a water cup, they were out. I asked them can I just use one of the soda cups? And he’s like, no I can’t give that to you there are cameras and I’ll get in trouble. (Seriously? But the cameras won’t see that I got water?) I say ok then, can you check in the back if you have more water cups? And he wasn’t even willing to go to the back to check. How indecent can someone be that a customer is thirsty and they just want water and they’re not willing to help them.

UPDATE: The new manager of this shop reached out to me to sincerely apologize and give me a refund, as well as to assure me that such shoddy service would not be tolerated under his management. I appreciate the gesture, and am willing to give this location another chance.  Every online order I've ever received from this shop (which is less than a mile away from me!), no matter which delivery service I use, has either been missing an item, lukewarm, or both. Not to mention their deliveries always take between 45 minutes and an hour, and again, I live less than a mile from the shop!!! Their app and website also give no option for refunds on missing items or feedback aside from a 1-5 star rating. Absolutely abysmal service. I'm out of patience with this location.

Absolutely disgusting, be very careful and inspect your food before you eat it! I came here tonight and ordered a chicken sandwich to go, I got home and something didn’t sit right with me when I noticed parts of the chicken pieces were dark and discolored. Chicken was dark, had gray spots, and looked spoiled and expired. I took out all the pieces and couldn’t eat anything. The broccoli cheddar soup looked very old and discolored also, very dark in color which indicates this store is using old product. This is not what you would get at Panera. Gave this place a try since I have not been here in a while. Very disappointed, wasted over $12.00 total and also could be facing food poising after they are serving this old, rotten chicken. The young blonde cashier also had a bad attitude and poor customer service, telling me to look at the sign when I asked a simple question of types of shakes. Never coming here again. I also have pictures of the rotten chicken which I will be emailing to the FDA to get this place inspected ASAP. This store needs a Food Safety Audit immediately!  Update— I emailed customer service TWICE as they suggest to on every response - have gotten no response. It has been over 2 weeks. Just another example of how terrible their customer service is.

This was the WORST experience I have ever had with ANY Potbellys EVER! **I eat at another Potbellys once or twice a week**  I placed an online order at around 830pm. I didnt think to question what time the store closed because it gave me multiple later options. I then received a call stating they were out of the soups I ordered and asked if I wanted something else. I ordered two different soups and chili. I asked for clarification, in disbelief, that they could be out of all three. I have someone go pick up the order and ask them to get something showing that they credited me back the amount of the soups. They could not show anything because it was an online order. I was upset given they had already processed the debit for the full amount. The manager on duty refused to put anything in writing that the money would be credited to my account and could not show anything in the system to prove it. At that point they were told to void the entire transaction and keep their food. BEST PART... They didnt have any of the soups because they had already pulled them for the night. Customer service isnt a priority. The employees are more concerned with getting out of there at 9pm on the dot.  I refuse to give them any business and would rather drive further to deal with people who understand customer service. I hope upper management takes note of what seem to be similar recurring issues within this location.

***Minorities  don't go to this place unless you want to be treated badly*** I'd have given them zero star if I had the option.  I wanted to share my DISAPPOINTING experience today at Potbelly @544N. Frederick Ave, Gaithersburg, MD 20887.  Potbelly used to be my favorite sandwich place for the past years, and I am not thinking to go back because of what happened:  After I got my sandwich and salad today and I went to check out. Cashier Ivonne asked what sandwich I got, so I told her "Turkey, Regular" clear and loud.  She heard me and she turned around and asked the girl who made my sandwich " what did she get?". And the girl confirmed what I said.  Then another customer (Caucasian, male) next to me was also at the check out. The other cashier just asked him what he got, did not ask the sandwich girl to confirm the answer, and went ahead to process his order.  After I questioned the way I was being treated differently. They threw away my salad and sandwich into the trash can in a very angry way in front of my face.  Anyone sees the problem here? I am being discriminated and treated badly. And the cashier Ivonne's attitude was very rude and unprofessional.  I am very disappointed and Potbelly you need to find a better way to train your employees. Learn how to respect each individual equally.  BTW, I have not heard back from Ivonne's manager Dave after I called this morning.
